    <h1>Science Project</h1>
        
    <h3>Firstly, let's talk about why oil damages the Earth.
    </h3>
        
<p>
Oil destroys the insulating ability of fur-bearing mammals, such as sea otters, and the water repellency of a bird's feathers, therefore disclosing these animals to brutal stuff. Without the power to repel water and protect it from cold water, birds and mammals will die from hypothermia.
</p>
    
